title: `models` directory disappeared in the latest commit
body_html:
The documentation refers to models/image/mnist/convolutional.py, however it doesn't exist anymore. It exists in r0.12, but not master. In fact, the whole models directory is missing. If restructuring is going on, I think the documentation has to be updated.

body:
The documentation refers to `models/image/mnist/convolutional.py`, however it doesn't exist anymore. It exists in `r0.12`, but not `master`. In fact, the whole `models` directory is missing. If restructuring is going on, I think the documentation has to be updated.

[Here is the documentation that refers to it](https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/blob/2e22f1b20/tensorflow/g3doc/get_started/os_setup.md#train-your-first-tensorflow-neural-net-model)
